modules.description: Converts an integer to a unique identifier type, ensuring type safety and preventing accidental misuse. Operates on a private integer type to enforce encapsulation and controlled usage. Used to generate and manage distinct entity identifiers in domain models.

Converts an integer to a specialized type representing placement values. Operates on the private integer type to enforce type safety in context-specific positioning logic. Used to manage grid coordinates and layout indices in user interface rendering.

Provides functions to encode and decode graphics protocol messages, including drawing commands and image handling. Works with byte sequences, integers, and custom data types representing graphical elements. Used to generate low-level protocol data for rendering text and images in terminal environments.

Encapsulates type-safe identifiers and placement values derived from integers, enabling precise control over entity references and layout positioning. Provides operations to convert and manipulate these types for use in terminal graphics rendering and user interface management. Supports tasks such as assigning unique object IDs and calculating grid-based positions. Examples include generating safe entity keys and handling coordinate-based layout calculations.
